description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an IT Support Technician to join the Shrewsbury and Telford Hospital Trust based at Shrewsbury Business Park.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have demonstrable experience in :-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;1st &lt;/span&gt;and 2nd line support and great troubleshooting skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;IT qualifications or working towards them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be well versed in Microsoft technologies from desktop, laptops and mobile device technologies such as iPads and associated applications with an understanding of networks, servers and cloud technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ideal candidate will have drive, determination, good customer service skills, be a good team worker with the desire and motivation to improve yourself and a positive can do attitude.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have what it takes, then this a great opportunity to further develop your career and join a committed team in a diverse, busy and fast moving technological environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDarren SladeJob titleEndpoint &amp; Licensing ManagerEmail addressDarren.slade@nhs.netTelephone number01952 282826&lt;/p&gt;
